Commentary: fuller on the stumps to the left-hand batsman, driven towards long-on and he's off the mark in T20Is
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najmul Hossain Shanto, 1 run

Commentary: fuller around off, driven inside out but couldn't beat extra cover
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: length ball angled in on to the pads, Liton looks to defend, an inside edge on to the pad
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, pushed down the ground, Ndlovu moves across to field himself
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: goes for the paddle sweep, was a touch fuller around off, Liton missed and an appeal for lbw but given not out. Zimbabwe want to review this. Replays show there was no bat involved but the impact was outside off, so Zimbabwe lose their review
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, digs it out towards long-on and he too is off the mark
fuller on the pads and flicked away behind square leg, the deep square leg fielder puts in a desperate dive but the ball just beats him
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball around off, punched towards point from the back foot
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: length ball around off, steers it towards point, dot again
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: floated outside off and Liton picks up the slower ball and smashes it over extra cover for one-bounce four
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball around off, punches it towards mid-off and hares to the other end for a quick single
fuller around off, whipped firmly but straight towards short midwicket
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najmul Hossain Shanto, no run

Commentary: backs away, smites it over his head! He'd made room before Ndlovu had delivered, and found the ball right in the slot, holding nothing back
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Liton Das, SIX runs

Commentary: picked up over the leg side now, Liton lets the bottom hand take the lead as he drags this from off stump into the leg side, placing it wide of long on
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Liton Das, FOUR runs

Commentary: down the ground! Ndlovu over-pitches outside off, and Liton steps out to swat him for another maximum down the ground
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Liton Das, SIX runs

Commentary: inside edge! Again Liton jumped down the track, but this time Ndlovu saw him coming and fired in a quicker one. He swipes across the line, and an inside edge ricochets just past the stumps and down to fine leg
quiet flick off the toes from Najmul, handing the strike back over
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Najmul Hossain Shanto, 1 run

Commentary: punched down the ground, and he ambles through for another single to keep the strike
length to start, just outside off at 133km/h, and it's dabbed down to third man
around the stumps comes Mpofu to the left-handed Najmul, but his line is too wide outside off
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Najmul Hossain Shanto, 1 wide

Commentary: too short, too wide, and Najmul is up on his tippy-toes to uppercut this over backward point. It lands just inside the boundary rope
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Najmul Hossain Shanto, FOUR runs

Commentary: that's better, Mpofu aiming fuller with this one and beating the outside edge. Decent pace too, up to 136km/h
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Najmul Hossain Shanto, no run

Commentary: angling in to Najmul, who taps to cover and sets off. Maruma is on the edge of the circle, and so the single is on
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Najmul Hossain Shanto, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball, an offcutter on the stumps, and Liton works across his pad to find a single to a diving short fine leg
full on the off stump to finish, and they pinch another quick single as Najmul drives to Williams at mid off
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Najmul Hossain Shanto, 1 run

Commentary: sliding stop saves a run! Jarvis over-pitches on his legs and is picked off down to fine leg. It looked like four all the way, but Burl charges across and puts in a dive to cut it off
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najmul Hossain Shanto, 3 runs

Commentary: makes room, carves through the covers! Liton is moving around a lot in the crease, and now he backs away to upset Jarvis' line, spanking him through the gap at cover
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, FOUR runs

Commentary: whoops, maybe he's moving around a little too much. Now he walks across to the off side, and Jarvis bursts a short one over his leg stump
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Liton Das, no run

Commentary: slower ball, down to 111km/h, but it's picked and flicked to midwicket for a single

leading edge, simple catch, and Zimbabwe have some relief. Jarvis delivered another offcutter, but Najmul didn't spot this one, glancing across it much too early. The ball spoons tamely off the leading edge of his bat, and Jarvis is in no trouble holding on to the simple chance
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Najmul Hossain Shanto, OUT
Dismissal_text: Najmul Hossain Shanto c & b Jarvis 11 (9b 1x4 0x6) SR: 122.22

Commentary: big shot, play and a miss! Jarvis delivers a pacy delivery just outside off, and Shakib flings the kitchen sink at it, hitting only fresh air
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Shakib Al Hasan, no run

Commentary: a touch too straight, and Liton flicks him just behind square to raise Bangladesh's fifty
crunched through cover, on the up. Shakib is off the mark in style, standing up to drive a wide length delivery through the gap at cover
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR runs

Commentary: angled in to him, and it's tapped to cover
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Shakib Al Hasan, no run

Commentary: glanced off the hip, just the one
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run

Commentary: stunning catch! Liton walks across to the off side and attempts a pick-up over fine leg. But he swipes underneath it and the ball balloons way, way into the sky off the leading edge. Madziva is at short fine leg and has plenty of ground to make, but he sprints back and tumbles into position under the ball, holding the catch cleanly
Dismissal_text: Liton Das c Madziva b Mpofu 38 (22b 4x4 2x6) SR: 172.72

Commentary: Mushfiqur is greeted with a bumper, ducking underneath a rising ball on middle stump
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: fetched from wide outside off, and down to long on
Commentary_short: Williams to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run

Commentary: speared in towards the pads, and Mushfiqur misses his glance but the ball comes off the pad, bouncing down to fine leg. He'd walked across his stumps, and that wasn't far away! But Zimbabwe have already burned their review. Ah, but replays show it was sliding down anyway
Commentary_short: Williams to Mushfiqur Rahim, 3 leg byes

Commentary: eased down to long on, one more
Commentary_short: Williams to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run

Commentary: hurled a bit too far down the leg side now
confusion! Mushfiqur flicks to square leg, Shakib calls for the single and sets off. It's his call, but Mushfiqur says no. Shakib turns and dives back to the crease. Tension in the middle
Commentary_short: Williams to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: quicker one, aimed at the stumps, and it keeps a little low. But Shakib's bat comes down in time, and he finds a single to midwicket
Commentary_short: Williams to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run

Commentary: slider to start, going across him, and it's cut just wide of the sweeper. They hurry back for the second
Commentary_short: Burl to Shakib Al Hasan, 2 runs

Commentary: chipped down Williams' throat! What kind of a shot was this? Shakib leaned forward and checked his drive at a full ball, lobbing it softly out to Williams at long off. He barely had to move, just walking in a few metres from the rope. There was no power at all behind the shot. Burl can't believe his luck. And Zimbabwe have another one!
Commentary_short: Burl to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Shakib Al Hasan c Williams b Burl 10 (9b 1x4 0x6) SR: 111.11

Commentary: emphatic! That's how Shakib should have played it. Mahmudullah steps out and gets to the pitch, throwing his hands into a lofted drive down the ground, clearing the straight boundary
a touch wide, but his dabbed cut goes straight to short third man
straighter this time, and he's picked off the pads for a single
much too short, and it's punished! Mushfiqur hops quickly onto the back, slamming a pull into the gap to the right of midwicket
Commentary_short: Burl to Mushfiqur Rahim, FOUR runs

Commentary: chopped down to short third man, no run there
quicker one, fired in at the off stump. It drifts in to Mahmudullah, who presents a straight bat in defence
nurdled into space on the leg side, just the single
full, outside off, and it's jammed out to the cover sweeper
too straight, glanced to deep backward square
nicely bowled, aimed at the off stump on an in-between length, Mushfiqur opts for defence
Commentary_short: Williams to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: floated down very full outside off, and it's chopped down past Mpofu at short third man. Mpofu is after it, hauling it in before the rope, albeit not very gracefully
another dab, this one goes straight to Mpofu
quicker one, just outside off. Tapped to point
floated up fuller, on middle and off. Mahmudullah has a good look and defends it back at him
a neat little drive sends the ball out to the cover sweeper, and as it's just wide of him there's time for a second
a bottom-edged cut bounces to Mpofu at short third man, another dot
legcutter to start, just outside off, and he's run down to third man for one
another slower cutter, around 118km/h, and it's worked down to long on
shot! Madziva is too full, outside off, with mid off up. Mushfiqur seizes the chance to drive down the ground. Didn't over hit it, but hit it well
Commentary_short: Madziva to Mushfiqur Rahim, FOUR runs

Commentary: the riposte is a bouncer, and he swivels to pull to fine leg
he jumps down the track at the bowler, swatting a back of a length delivery back past him. The umpire takes evasive action
short again, and sitting up outside off. Mushfiqur lifts a cut over the infield, but third man is around to cut it off
he backs away before the ball is delivered, but Ndlovu follows him and he can only flick to midwicket, in the deep
reverse sweep, and there's a stifled appeal as he doesn't quite connect! But he does manage to get a touch on it, given as runs
speared in to the pads, and he's worked out to deep midwicket
slog sweep, into the gap! There are two men out on the leg side in that direction, but he placed a big shot perfectly, bending down low
Commentary_short: Ndlovu to Mushfiqur Rahim, FOUR runs

Commentary: and now he sets himself for a paddle-scoop, but the ball comes off the toe end of the bat and rolls wide of mid on instead
quick and flat, on his pads, and it's glanced to deep midwicket

lifted over long on! This was a slog sweep, and it went miles in the air. It almost went higher than it did far, and Mutombodzi thought he was in with a shout down at long on, but the ball has just enough on it to beat his leap on the boundary
flicked off the toes, just the one
Mushfiqur jumps down but Williams spots him, pulling his length back. Dabbed to third man
Commentary_short: Williams to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: pushed too far down the leg side, called wide
and now he aims wide of off, ripping one past Mushfiqur, who had backed away to leg
Commentary_short: Williams to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: on the drive now, down to long off. Sharp work from Burl keeps them to one
quicker one, speared in flat and fast. Mushfiqur wants two, but Mahmudullah turns him down and he has to scurry back to make his ground
very full, on his toes, and he's flicked out to deep midwicket
floated up wide outside off, and he throws himself into an aerial drive. The ball skims into the ground in the outfield and Ndlovu has some work to do
attempted switch hit, but the ball fizzes past him into Taylor's gloves
nicely bowled, full and straight. Tino also fields well off his own bowling, diving across towards mid on
flayed over long off! This was in the slot, and Mahmudullah's eyes lit up. He read the length well, and held nothing back in the stroke
legbreak, a touch wide outside off, but the cover sweeper cleans up and keeps them to one
cutter to start, but it goes just down the leg side. If Mahmdullah had stayed in his normal position, he would probably have glanced that, but he'd walked across to the off side
a yorker now, and it's dug out into the leg side
short one, and it gets a little big on Mushfiqur, who hurries a pull into the deep
another slower cutter, down to 117km/h, and they take a tip-and-run single into the leg side
slog sweep, over the rope! This time he was expecting the offcutter, Mushfiqur bending down low and picking it up powerfully over deep backward square
Commentary_short: Mpofu to Mushfiqur Rahim, SIX runs

Commentary: dropped! Mpofu dug in a short one, down the leg side, and the ball kissed the glove on the way through. Taylor dived to his left, but spilled the chance. Mpofu has his hands on his head
good running, as he clips the ball into space on the leg side. The fielder is right on the boundary, and they hurry through for a second
eased down to long on
swept, and top edged, but it lands safely and bounces away to the boundary! He got enough on it to beat short fine leg, inside the circle
quicker one, and slightly shorter too. Glanced off the hip
attempted reverse sweep, but the ball rushes past the shot outside off
Commentary_short: Williams to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: another quicker one, very quick at 110km/h, hurrying his jab down to long on
fuller, straighter, and it keeps a little low too, but Mahmudullah is in no trouble pushing it down to long on
legbreak, wide outside off, and it's fetched down to long on with a bit of an ungainly swipe
beaten, outside off, by another legbreak. It was the bounce that did it
Commentary_short: Mutombodzi to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: gone this time! Excellent work by Taylor behind the stumps. Mushfiqur swipes across the line at another one that bursts off a length, getting a thin top edge. The ball bounces up at Taylor, who parries it to his left and then grasps it at the second attempt. A difficult chance, but he's held on
Dismissal_text: Mushfiqur Rahim c †Taylor b Mutombodzi 32 (26b 3x4 1x6) SR: 123.07

Commentary: full toss, on leg stump, and it's clipped into the leg side
quicker one, outside off, and it's pulled off the front foot down to long on
slider, on off stump, and they pick up a quick single with a dab to point
back of a length and rising on middle and off, Afif chopping a cut straight to point
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Afif Hossain, no run

Commentary: bouncer now, and it jumps past Afif's pull. It was a slower bouncer, around 120km/h
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Afif Hossain, no run

Commentary: an attempted yorker slips out as a full toss, and it's sliced off the outside half of the bat down to third man, Madziva diving in that position to save runs
another full toss, outside off, and it's slugged down to long off

another full toss, swung into the leg side, and it comes to ground just in front of Sean Williams, running in and then diving forward. He couldn't get there to take the catch, but did well to save runs as Bangladesh's 150 comes up
another full toss, on his legs, and it's swatted into the leg side. They hurry back for the second.

legcutter, outside off, and Mahmudullah is up to all sorts of tricks in the crease. He sets himself for a paddle-scoop, then moves across to off for a reverse. In the end the ball rushes past him outside off
short, and pulled into the stands! This time he stayed still in the crease, rocking back and slugging a muscular pull well over the rope to bring up his fifty
fuller this time, and he's on the drive down to long on

edged, and caught! Afif steps to leg, making room, and aims a flashing drive into the covers. But he has to reach for it, and ends up feathering an edge through to Taylor, who tumbles to his left to hold on
Dismissal_text: Afif Hossain c †Taylor b Mpofu 7 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 87.50

Commentary: slower legcutter, outside off at 113km/h, and it's cracked to point

picked up over fine leg! This wasn't such a bad delivery, Mpofu slightly missing his mark attempting a yorker. It slipped out as a low full toss, dipping in towards his toes, but Mahmudullah got down low to lift it cleanly over fine leg
another low full toss, chipped down to long off
nicely bowled, a yorker on middle, but excellent running brings two as it's dug out to long on

another full toss, and he picks out the fielder! Mahmudullah was aiming for the stands beyond midwicket, but couldn't get enough on it, picking out Williams near the rope. The umpires want to have another look at this, as the full toss was quite high ... but replays show it was dipping just under waist height, and he's got to go.
Dismissal_text: Mahmudullah c Williams b Jarvis 62 (41b 1x4 5x6) SR: 151.21

Commentary: action replay! Another high full toss, another swipe into the leg side, and he gets more height than distance to pick out the fielder. With two rank full tosses, Jarvis is on a hat-trick!
Dismissal_text: Mosaddek Hossain c Chakabva b Jarvis 2 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

Commentary: not this time, as he digs this one in short and it's pulled off the front foot, down to long on. Again they take on the fielder for the second run. Should he have gone for another high full toss?
another short one, hammered to the fence! He was deep in the crease, waiting for it, and cracks a big pull into the gap on the leg side to finish the innings off
Commentary_short: Jarvis to Mohammad Saifuddin, FOUR runs

Commentary: fuller around off, a hint of away movement, pushed towards cover from the crease
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length outside off, Taylor is trying to stay leg side of the ball, steers it towards cover once again
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball outside off, once again staying at the leg stump, pushes it towards cover for the third time in three balls
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Taylor, no run

Commentary: pitched up and hit firmly, straight towards the bowler who gets his left foot in the line of the ball to make the stop
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Taylor, no run

Commentary: length ball around off, Taylor looks to go over the top but ends up toe-ending it, and as a result gets only the height and not the distance, Shakib settles under it at mid-off
Dismissal_text: BRM Taylor c Shakib Al Hasan b Mohammad Saifuddin 0 (5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: first run for Zimbabwe. A length ball around off, moving away from the batsman who pushes it towards third man
length ball, angling in with the arm, takes the inner half of the bat as Masakadza was looking to push it, a single to square leg
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: length ball outside off, pushed towards covers
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Chakabva, no run

Commentary: tossed up on the stumps, Chakabva comes down the track and looks to go over wide long-on, misses and the ball sneaks in through the gate to hit the middle stump. Zimbabwe 2 for 2 in the second over
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Chakabva, OUT
Dismissal_text: RW Chakabva  b Shakib Al Hasan 0 (2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: length ball around off, tucked away towards short midwicket
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Williams, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, lunges forward and pushes it towards long-off
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Williams, 1 run

Commentary: almost played on! Was a length ball outside off, Masakadza was looking to play it through covers, away from the body, gets an inside edge on to the back pad
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, coming in to the left-hander, pushes it towards mid-on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Williams, no run

Commentary: a touch fuller outside off, pushes it towards deep point for one
a touch fuller around off, comes forward and defends it towards covers
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: length ball on the stumps this time, Masakadza comes forward and pushes it towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: fuller outside off this time, Masakadza comes forward and smashes it between the bowler and the mid-off for a much-needed boundary
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: pulls his length back a bit, a hint of away movement, comes forward and defends
Commentary_short: Mohammad Saifuddin to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: and strikes straightaway! Was a short of length angling across, Williams goes for the pull but is cramped and ends up slicing it towards midwicket, Afif comes forward and takes it comfortably. Zimbabwe reeling at 8 for 3
Dismissal_text: SC Williams c Afif Hossain b Shafiul Islam 2 (5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 40.00

Commentary: length ball outside off, punched towards cover from the back foot
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: short of length outside off, another back-foot punch, this time to the right of Afif who slides across and prevents any runs
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: too short this time and even though it was outside off, Masakadza just dragged it wide of mid-on for four
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: chopped between cover and extra cover, needling the gap this time, was a length ball outside off and Masakadza just latched on to it
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Masakadza, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball around off, punched from the crease but this time straight to the extra cover fielder
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: a huge appeal for lbw but denied. Length ball around off, slower in the air, Mutombodzi was looking to come down the ground but had to change his mind, struck on the front pad but outside the line of the off stump
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Mutombodzi, no run
Shakib Al Hasan to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: skips down again and works it in front of the square leg for one
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: Masakadza too gives charge, Shakib once again slows down his pace but Masakadza goes with the shot and just clears the mid-on, scampers back for the third
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, 3 runs

Commentary: slower outside off, dragging his length back as he sees batsman coming down, dragged towards square leg
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Mutombodzi, 1 run

Commentary: once again slower through the air, Masakadza was looking to force it through the off side but this is angled in at the batsman, a single to mid-on off the inner half
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Masakadza, 1 run

Commentary: a great take by Mushfiqur as this was bowled on a length down the leg side, called a wide
length ball around off, dabbed towards cover-point for one
beaten! Length ball angling across the batsman who was looking to play it towards wide mid-on, misses
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Mutombodzi, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, comes forward and flicks it towards deep midwicket for a couple
short of length on the pads, tucked away towards deep square leg this time
length ball on middle and leg, comes forward and flicks it towards midwicket

Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Mutombodzi, SIX runs

Commentary: fuller around off, chops it into the ground towards covers
Commentary_short: Aminul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, comes forward and drills it towards long-off
and he gets a wicket in his very first over. Was fuller around off, Mutombodzi looked to go over long-off but failed to get the timing right and Najmul takes it comfortably near the boundary
Dismissal_text: CT Mutombodzi c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Aminul Islam 11 (9b 0x4 1x6) SR: 122.22

Commentary: fuller around off, tossed up a bit, Masakadza hits it down the ground, the bowler moves across to make the stop
Commentary_short: Aminul Islam to Masakadza, no run

Commentary: fuller on the stumps, hits it firmly towards the bowler who gets a hand to it but cannot stop the single
length ball on the pads, tucked away behind square leg for one
short of length at the batsman who defends it from the back foot
Commentary_short: Shafiul Islam to Burl, no run

Commentary: played on! Burl departs! Length ball just outside off, Burl was playing away from the body, just pushing at it, gets an inside edge that ricochets onto the stumps off his thigh. Half the Zimbabwe side are already back in the pavilion in the eight over
Dismissal_text: RP Burl  b Shafiul Islam 1 (3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

Commentary: length ball outside off, comes forward a bit and guides it towards third man
short and wide outside off, smashed but there is sweeper cover in place
length ball outside off, tapped towards backward point, the fielder dives to his left to make the stop
short of length outside off, punched towards the right of mid-off from the back foot
tossed up around off, smashed back towards the bowler who makes a partial stop

Commentary: length ball outside off, steers it towards covers for one
goes for the reverse sweep but the Aminul has thrown at wide outside off and perhaps too wide outside off, called a wide
length ball on the stumps, pulled towards deep-backward square leg

fuller on the stumps, misses the sweep and is struck on the thigh. That's as plumb as it gets. Masakadza is having a chat with his partner but he knows there is no hope and walks back as the timer ends
Dismissal_text: H Masakadza lbw b Aminul Islam 25 (25b 3x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: length ball outside off, punched towards deep extra cover off the back foot
fuller outside off from wide of the crease, pushes at it, gets a thick outside edge past the first slip
fuller around off, comes forward and pushes it towards mid-off

Commentary: length ball on the pads, pulled away towards fine leg
length ball around off, stays deep in his crease and lofts it over wide long-on, fifty comes up for Zimbabwe

Commentary: short of length at the batsman who sways away and guides it towards third man
a bouncer this time, catches the batsman by surprise who manages to duck under at the very last moment
Commentary_short: Mustafizur Rahman to Madziva, no run

Commentary: a slower length ball outside off, steered towards third man
uses his feet to works this full toss from outside off towards long-on
fuller around off, goes for the reverse sweep and almost ends up guiding it on to the stumps, goes through the keeper's legs
conventional sweep this time, misses and huge appeal for lbw, was spinning away and would have missed off

Commentary: length ball on the stumps, comes forward and pushes it back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Aminul Islam to Madziva, no run

Commentary: fuller around off, pushes it towards extra cover, goes through the fielder and they come back for the second before long-off comes across
a low full toss on the stumps, worked towards wide long-on but only a single
length ball around off, goes for the sweep but is early into the shot, the bottom hand comes off the Madziva drags the ball towards short fine leg

Commentary: Mutumbami goes for the sweep as well, much better connection and a single to fine leg

Commentary: looks to come down the track and work it on the leg side, misses but gets a leg-bye to short fine

Commentary: goes for the reverse sweep, is early into the shot, the ball hits the glove and goes on to rap him on the pads
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Mutumbami, no run

Commentary: worked away towards deep square leg this time for one
Commentary_short: Shakib Al Hasan to Mutumbami, 1 run

Commentary: flatter and quicker on the stumps, flicked towards backward square leg
